It is difficult to generalize the interests and obsessions of all kids in East Timor, as individual preferences can vary greatly. However, like in many other parts of the world, some common obsessions among kids in East Timor may include:

1. Technology and gadgets: With the increasing availability of smartphones, tablets, and other electronic devices, many kids in East Timor, like elsewhere, may be obsessed with technology, social media, and online gaming.

2. Pop culture: Kids in East Timor, like in many other countries, may be obsessed with popular music, movies, TV shows, and celebrities. They may follow international trends and idolize popular figures.

3. Sports: Football (soccer) is a popular sport in East Timor, and many kids may be obsessed with playing, watching, and supporting their favorite teams and players. Other sports such as basketball, volleyball, and martial arts may also attract their interest.

4. Fashion and trends: Kids in East Timor, particularly in urban areas, may be interested in fashion and keeping up with the latest trends. They may follow international fashion brands and styles.

5. Gaming: Video games, both online and offline, have gained popularity among kids worldwide, and East Timor is no exception. Many kids may be obsessed with gaming and spend a significant amount of time playing and exploring different games.
